cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM 

The paper deals with rare event detection from image pairs, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a novel method for learning disentangled representations, which involves training a neural network. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of negative samples, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with satellite images, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
